rce/Zara_Tindall\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zara Tindall\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zara_Tindall\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zara_Tindall\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only daughter of Princess Anne and Captain Mark Phillips won a silver medal in Team Eventing at the 2012 London Olympics and is one of the country's leading equestrian riders.\", \"from\": 331, \"to\": 510, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 370, \"end\": 391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Phillips\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Captain Mark Phillips\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Phillips\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Phillips\"}, {\"begin\": 492, \"end\": 502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"score\": 0.891615660303938, \"rank\": 0.12150192147220609, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tindall, 43, confirmed to Vogue in 2022 that she was back in training in the hopes of earning a spot in the Paris squad and taking another run at a gold medal.\", \"from\": 512, \"to\": 671, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 538, \"end\": 543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Vogue\", \"score\": 0.9999998983955771, \"rank\": 1.009476182405501e-07, \"text\": \"Vogue\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Vogue\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Vogue\"}, {\"begin\": 620, \"end\": 625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999610938638, \"rank\": 3.890622262075133e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the British Olympics committee have confirmed the eventing team representing Great Britain in the French capital will be Rosalind Canter, Laura Collett, Tom McEwen, and Yasmin Ingham.\", \"from\": 673, \"to\": 865, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 686, \"end\": 693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9539450329171312, \"rank\": 0.028718527540313423, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 759, \"end\": 772, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9912143044882368, \"rank\": 0.008863567101559477, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 780, \"end\": 786, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.4484823758735515, \"rank\": 0.7563522428462459, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 820, \"end\": 833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\", \"score\": 0.9999948522784671, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laura Collett\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\"}, {\"begin\": 835, \"end\": 845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_McEwen_(drag_racer)\", \"score\": 0.8873196584610349, \"rank\": 0.07814407814407483, \"text\": \"Tom McEwen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q378622\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_McEwen_(drag_racer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_McEwen_(drag_racer)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The decision marks the fifth non-consecutive Olympics where Tindall has been left off the Team GB squad.\", \"from\": 867, \"to\": 971, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 957, \"end\": 964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999997781456178, \"rank\": 1.6991414638743035e-07, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tindall missed the 2004 Athens and 2008 Beijing games because of injuries to her horse.\", \"from\": 973, \"to\": 1060, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 992, \"end\": 1003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9990170303831384, \"rank\": 0.0009839367953518364, \"text\": \"2004 Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1008, \"end\": 1020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9994859017314379, \"rank\": 0.0005141882577761807, \"text\": \"2008 Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2016, Tindall technically qualified for the 2016 Rio Olympics but was left off the final squad due to more concerns over her horse's fitness.\", \"from\": 1062, \"to\": 1206, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The eldest granddaughter of Queen Elizabeth II opted out of qualifying for the 2020 Tokyo Olympics, which occurred around the time of the birth of her third child.\", \"from\": 1208, \"to\": 1371, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1236, \"end\": 1254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.29280073370369e-12, \"text\": \"Queen Elizabeth II\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\"}, {\"begin\": 1242, \"end\": 1254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.094030306946014e-17, \"text\": \"Elizabeth II\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both of Zara parents were also pro-equestrians and Olympians but Tindall was the first ever British royal to win a medal.\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1465, \"end\": 1472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9539450329171312, \"rank\": 0.028718527540313423, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Anne competed in the 1976 Montreal Olympics as an equestrian but missed out on a medal after falling off her horse Goodwill and cracking a vertebrae.\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1645, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1546, \"end\": 1556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"score\": 0.891615660303938, \"rank\": 0.12150192147220609, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, Zara's dad Captain Phillips won two gold medals at the 1972 Munich Games and 1988 Seoul Games in Team Eventing.\", \"from\": 1647, \"to\": 1769, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1658, \"end\": 1662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zara_Tindall\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.090925675912681e-31, \"text\": \"Zara\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zara_Tindall\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zara_Tindall\"}, {\"begin\": 1669, \"end\": 1685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Captain_Phillips_(film)\", \"score\": 0.9999987765848554, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Captain Phillips\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Captain_Phillips_(film)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Captain_Phillips_(film)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The update comes just weeks afteran unnamed source inside Buckingham Palace revealed the Tindalls were the \\\"glue of their generation of royals\\\" following Kate and Charles's cancer diagnoses.\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1961, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1925, \"end\": 1929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\", \"score\": 0.8558059950699652, \"rank\": 0.13899984651765993, \"text\": \"Kate\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\"}, {\"begin\": 1934, \"end\": 1941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\", \"score\": 0.9570260452235089, \"rank\": 0.04482035805241154, \"text\": \"Charles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zara and her husband Mike, 45, a retired rugby great, are fiercely loyal to the monarchy and have reportedly cut ties with Prince Harry and Meghan Markle for betraying Charles.\", \"from\": 1963, \"to\": 2139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1963, \"end\": 1967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zara_Tindall\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.090925675912681e-31, \"text\": \"Zara\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zara_Tindall\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zara_Tindall\"}, {\"begin\": 2086, \"end\": 2098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resour